                    <msContents>
                        <summary>
                            <p>دیوان نفعی</p>
                            <p>The poetical works of Nefi of Erzerúm, who flourished in the reign of Sultán
                                Murad IV and was put to death, according to most authorities, in 1044/1634-5
                                (Hist. of Ottoman Poetry, vol. III, p. 252 foll.). See Rieu, B.M.T.C., p. 192</p>
                            <p>Ff. 1-60 comprise Persian qasidas, ghazals, and qit'as, beginning:</p>
                            <p>The Turkish poems (ff. 62-214) begin:</p>
                            <p>نگوید نشنود هر دو جز از توحید یزدانش دلم سرمست جام عشق و عقل كل زباندانش</p>
                            <p>سلك تسبیح در سبع المثانیدر سوزم عقده سررشته راز نهانیدر سوزم</p>
                            <p>Ff. 214 of 18 x 12.5 cm and 15 ll. Good ta'liq with rubrications. No colophon or
                                date. Bought from J. J. Naaman in May, 1902.</p>
                        </summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="W_3-item1">
